<subSubSection id="C304652A4D20324DFF2746FFFBA03036" pageId="2" pageNumber="579" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA136A14D20324DFF2746FFFBA03036" blockId="2.[151,1437,402,1329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D20324DFF2746FFFE8C31C3" bold="true" box="[199,338,1194,1220]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Comments:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="54A588034D20324DFE7146FEFE3631C2" box="[401,488,1195,1221]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">syntype</typeStatus>
series on which the species was based includes members of 2 species. Therefore, according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B504D20324DFEC9469AFE6B31EE" author="ICZN" box="[297,437,1231,1257]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579" refId="ref5529" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN (1999</bibRefCitation>
, Art. 74.1, 74.7) the 
<typeStatus id="54A588034D20324DFD7B469AFCDC31EE" box="[667,770,1231,1257]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">lectotype</typeStatus>
(male) is here designated to become the name-bearing type of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D224D20324DFF5846A6FDA7300A" authority="Gorham, 1884" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1884" box="[184,633,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Calocladon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiriquense">
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D20324DFF5846A6FE16300A" box="[184,456,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Calocladon chiriquense</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B504D20324DFE3146A6FDA7300A" author="Gorham, H. S." box="[465,633,1267,1293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579" pagination="225 - 272" refId="ref5500" refString="Gorham, H. S. (1884) Malacodermata. Fam. Lycidae. Biologia Centrali-Americana, 3 (2), Supplement, 225 - 272." type="journal article" year="1884">Gorham, 1884</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Simultaneously, 
<specimenCount id="9D18FD284D20324DFCA446A6FC20300A" box="[836,1022,1267,1293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579" type="generic" typeStatus="paralectotypes">3 paralectotypes</specimenCount>
(
<specimenCount id="9D18FD284D20324DFBF046A6FBB2300A" box="[1040,1132,1267,1293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579" type="male">2 males</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount id="9D18FD284D20324DFB9A46A6FB3E3009" box="[1146,1248,1267,1294]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579" type="female">1 female</specimenCount>
) are designated, while remaining 
<typeStatus id="54A588034D20324DFEB54742FE693036" box="[341,439,1303,1329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">syntypes</typeStatus>
belong to a new genus a description of which is in preparation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
